__DESCRIPTION__

New programmers all forgot about bits and bytes. Some of our core modules are more broken than you expect.

* [Parity-bits](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parity_bit) to recognized errors
* [CRC-Codes](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cyclic_redundancy_check) - to even fix errors
* Crypto Checksums: [MD4](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MD4), [MD5](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MD5), [SHA1](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SHA1), [SHA256](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SHA256)  - "one way functions", "hashing"
* Some suggestions at the end of the presentation

See the [Reddit](http://www.reddit.com/r/perl/comments/28pefy/digestsha_is_broken_20_min_presentation/) discussiong and the [rejected bug report](https://rt.cpan.org/Public/Bug/Display.html?id=93139)
